    <note>Song(2) Daofang [10044]  zi Yi(righteousness)shu alternate to Yishu mentioned as father-in-law of Wang Kuang's [10043]. There is a funerary inscription for Daofang in Xu Han, WJ, 12.5a-7a, which confirms this relationship (Kuang was his eldest daughter's husband. She was dead by 1118) . This source also for appointment in 1113 as Jiangshi lang, Taiyi xueyu (Lecturer in the Imperial Medical College). His first son, Gongjui [24331], was appointed Sizhou Facao canjun on Daofang's death, whereas his brother, Gongrong [24332] was not in office. Daofang's other daughters all married local residents (xiangli). Daofang's father, Kede [24330], was a recluse (yunju), who studied such things as astronomy (xingli), the five phases (wuxing), etc. wife's surname was Sun, second wife was Ren. CBD, 1, 779.From Hartwell's ACTIVITY table:1113:  Appointed Jiangshi lang, Taiyi xueyu (Instructor in the Imperial Medical College).</note>
